docs.lead_paragraph: JAMES LANE ALLEN, whose "Choir Invisible" and "Kentucky Cardinal" are among the classics of American fiction, has written another tale of the Kentucky he knows so well, a whimsical story of youth's great adventure, called "The Kentucky Warbler," which Dotbleday, Page Co. will publish in mid-January.
